1
00:00:03,470 --> 00:00:05,450
<i>You're the one who poisoned the bride,</i>

2
00:00:06,130 --> 00:00:07,410
<i>are you not?</i>

3
00:00:07,410 --> 00:00:09,530
<i>Perhaps you felt particularly vengeful.</i>

4
00:00:09,530 --> 00:00:12,300
<i>What's your next plot?</i>

5
00:00:12,950 --> 00:00:15,690
<i>Will you test your luck again?</i>

6
00:00:15,690 --> 00:00:17,200
Shut your damn mouth.

7
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,650
You sat next to Sayaka at the ceremony,

8
00:00:29,650 --> 00:00:35,740
and took the opportunity to poison her.

9
00:00:35,740 --> 00:00:38,710
Isn't that why you've avoided the police?

10
00:00:38,710 --> 00:00:40,130
Why would I poison my own wife?

11
00:00:40,130 --> 00:00:44,230
Perhaps you already knew of Sayaka's past.

12
00:00:44,230 --> 00:00:45,450
Of course not!

13
00:00:45,450 --> 00:00:48,500
I hear you're obsessed
with the idea of "pure love".

14
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,970
Your nosy coworker told me all about it.

15
00:00:50,970 --> 00:00:56,920
Yet your very wife turned to other men
to ease her lonely heart.

16
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:59,290
No, Sayaka would never.

17
00:00:59,910 --> 00:01:01,980
That's exactly why you're so suspicious.

18
00:01:02,580 --> 00:01:06,100
You only see people
for who they are on the surface.

19
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:09,390
You think a mere fraction of their nature

20
00:01:09,390 --> 00:01:12,480
defines their very being.

21
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:17,920
Have you ever thought about why your wife

22
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:21,000
engaged in these "flings" to comfort herself?

23
00:01:21,980 --> 00:01:24,380
You haven't, have you?

24
00:01:24,380 --> 00:01:26,780
You know nothing about us.

25
00:01:26,780 --> 00:01:28,730
No, I don't.

26
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:34,750
But I do know humans who feel empty inside

27
00:01:34,750 --> 00:01:39,980
often let their emotions take the reigns.

28
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:48,160
I...

29
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:50,990
You couldn't forgive Sayaka
for her past actions.

30
00:01:52,660 --> 00:01:58,470
You won't even accept her for who she is.

31
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:05,110
That's the biggest reason why I suspect you.

32
00:02:31,830 --> 00:02:33,990
<i>I couldn't forgive her?</i>

33
00:02:35,610 --> 00:02:37,480
<i>I'm not accepting her?</i>

34
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,660
Kazu?

35
00:02:55,930 --> 00:02:57,910
Yeah?

36
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:03,250
What time will you be getting back today?

37
00:03:06,490 --> 00:03:09,040
I'll check my schedule,
and text you about it.

38
00:03:12,470 --> 00:03:13,800
Morning.

39
00:03:15,230 --> 00:03:16,840
Yeah.

40
00:03:17,850 --> 00:03:19,410
What's up?

41
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,120
Kazuomi.

42
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:37,990
I'm here if you need to talk, alright?

43
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:47,530
Naoto, are you free tonight?

44
00:03:47,530 --> 00:03:49,750
[Sorry, I've got overtime today.]
[I'll be eating out for dinner.]

45
00:04:00,410 --> 00:04:02,730
Are you going to be a statue all night?

46
00:04:02,730 --> 00:04:05,400
Come on, dig in.

47
00:04:07,970 --> 00:04:10,430
That rumor's still eating at you, isn't it?

48
00:04:11,330 --> 00:04:14,170
I'm telling you, it was that photographer.

49
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:18,790
Chin up, man. You'll make Sayaka worry.

50
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,070
Sayaka...

51
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,590
There you are.

52
00:04:22,590 --> 00:04:23,930
- 'Sup.
- Hey there.

53
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:26,130
What's up, Kazuomi?

54
00:04:26,130 --> 00:04:27,420
Makoto?

55
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:32,050
I thought a hype guy like him
would help cheer you up.

56
00:04:32,050 --> 00:04:34,440
Looks delicious.

57
00:04:35,050 --> 00:04:37,750
- I'm taking one.
- Hey!

58
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:51,660
Now that hits the spot.

59
00:04:55,610 --> 00:04:57,270
What's with the glum face?

60
00:04:57,270 --> 00:05:02,800
Rumors about his wedding
are circulating around the office.

61
00:05:05,810 --> 00:05:07,360
Oh, shoot.

62
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,170
Wait, my bad.

63
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:10,890
What?

64
00:05:13,060 --> 00:05:14,890
I might've started those rumors.

65
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:16,470
- What?
- You?

66
00:05:16,470 --> 00:05:22,320
Yeah. I mentioned the whole ordeal
when I went drinking the other day.

67
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,450
Dude...

68
00:05:23,450 --> 00:05:26,580
Pretty sure there was an official
from town hall there.

69
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:29,640
Damn, didn't think it'd spread.

70
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,720
Could we get another beer, please?

71
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,380
Coming right up.`

72
00:05:33,380 --> 00:05:36,900
You didn't stop to think
how Kazuomi would feel?

73
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:40,380
I didn't think it'd spread.

74
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:42,670
Seriously, my bad.

75
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:45,880
I wasn't trying to cause you trouble.

76
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:48,000
Blame the alcohol, you know?

77
00:05:50,260 --> 00:05:52,910
Sorry, forgive me. Please?

78
00:05:52,910 --> 00:05:54,610
I mean it.

79
00:05:54,610 --> 00:06:00,210
Guess I was off my mark
about the photographer.

80
00:06:00,210 --> 00:06:03,940
Photographer? Whatever, let's get grilling.

81
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:21,100
Forgive the guy, Kazuomi. He apologized.

82
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,830
You trusted him enough
to invite him to your wedding.

83
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:27,560
I know that.

84
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:36,780
I'm saying this for your sake, alright?

85
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:43,610
Tolerance is an important trait to have.

86
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,310
Kazuomi.

87
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:06,020
Grow up already.

88
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:17,820
"Grow up", huh?

89
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:22,210
Is that what it'll take to forgive him?

90
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:29,050
<i>If possible, could you please assist me?</i>

91
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:32,140
<i>Assist you, in finding the culprit?</i>

92
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,620
<i>Please help me, for Sayaka's sake.</i>

93
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:05,040
<i>Please, I beg you.</i>

94
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:18,840
[Kazuomi Hayashida]

95
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:32,360
Sayaka.

96
00:08:38,570 --> 00:08:40,180
Sayaka?

97
00:08:44,180 --> 00:08:46,130
<i>Your beloved wife</i>

98
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:47,890
<i>has a history.</i>

99
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:50,400
<i>She's seen other men in her life.</i>

100
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,340
<i>She worked part-time at a ConCafe.</i>

101
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:56,010
<i>She had relationships with her customers.</i>

102
00:09:00,370 --> 00:09:02,600
Damn it!

103
00:09:12,580 --> 00:09:15,850
Kazu?

104
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,540
You're home already?

105
00:09:20,540 --> 00:09:24,190
I thought you wouldn't be back yet.

106
00:09:27,290 --> 00:09:29,170
Did you go out somewhere?

107
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:35,580
Yeah, I went shopping.

108
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:37,180
Alone?

109
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:41,750
Yup.

110
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:53,840
Sayaka.

111
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,550
Why did you dress yourself up?

112
00:09:58,550 --> 00:10:00,980
Were you fooling around with other men?

113
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:03,980
Finding matches on dating apps, even?

114
00:10:08,010 --> 00:10:12,850
I didn't take you... for such an easy woman.

115
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,640
Sayaka.

116
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,520
Yes?

117
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:32,210
I wanted to ask.

118
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:37,440
<i>You couldn't forgive Sayaka.</i>

119
00:10:38,990 --> 00:10:40,880
<i>Grow up already.</i>

120
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,690
What's wrong?

121
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:51,450
Is it something serious?

122
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:57,200
<i>Interrogating her about her past</i>

123
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:03,170
<i>won't resolve anything.</i>

124
00:11:03,170 --> 00:11:05,060
Kazu?

125
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:18,990
<i>I wonder if Sayaka
really wanted to become a violinist.</i>

126
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,840
Sayaka.

127
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:27,190
Did you really want to become a violinist?

128
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:29,090
Huh?

129
00:11:29,090 --> 00:11:32,830
Sorry, it's just something
I've been wondering about.

130
00:11:32,830 --> 00:11:38,170
Maybe you felt reluctant
to play at our ceremony as well?

131
00:11:43,650 --> 00:11:45,500
I see.

132
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:49,160
So you noticed.

133
00:11:54,080 --> 00:12:00,340
I can't keep any secrets from you, can I?

134
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:05,870
That's right.

135
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:10,000
I...

136
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:16,370
I never once wanted to become a violinist.

137
00:12:17,830 --> 00:12:23,160
But my mother insisted.

138
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,840
She believed I could become a professional.

139
00:12:29,650 --> 00:12:32,750
I only wanted to meet her expectations.

140
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:38,430
So I practiced every day,
without ever going out with friends.

141
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:40,640
I worked hard.

142
00:12:42,180 --> 00:12:43,650
But eventually...

143
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:51,430
I stopped getting first at recitals.

144
00:12:52,930 --> 00:12:59,150
Practice got tougher.

145
00:13:04,690 --> 00:13:06,450
So you know what I did?

146
00:13:11,140 --> 00:13:13,650
In elementary school...

147
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:20,870
I broke a bone during P.E.

148
00:13:24,010 --> 00:13:25,550
I...

149
00:13:35,450 --> 00:13:38,050
I broke that bone on purpose.

150
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:45,070
All so I wouldn't have to play
the violin anymore.

151
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:52,990
I'm awful, aren't I?

152
00:13:52,990 --> 00:13:56,300
My mother was only encouraging me.

153
00:13:59,810 --> 00:14:02,550
That's enough, Sayaka.

154
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:04,330
I get it now.

155
00:14:04,330 --> 00:14:06,780
Do you feel...

156
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:12,080
disillusioned, hearing all this?

157
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:14,350
Of course not.

158
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,650
No matter what you do.

159
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:23,420
no matter what you've done in the past,

160
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:27,430
I will accept you, for all that you are.

161
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:39,550
Married couples share both the good
and the bad with each other.

162
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:48,660
<i>Sayaka is surrounded by hypocrites.</i>

163
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:52,230
<i>People come to take advantage of her.</i>

164
00:14:53,310 --> 00:14:58,660
<i>Yet every time, Sayaka never berates them.</i>

165
00:14:58,660 --> 00:15:05,090
<i>She instead finds a way to blame herself.</i>

166
00:15:09,740 --> 00:15:12,960
Even if everyone in the world turns on you,

167
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:17,300
I alone will be your ally, alright?

168
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:26,170
<i>The one I ought to protect...</i>

169
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,680
<i>is the Sayaka I see right now.</i>

170
00:15:33,810 --> 00:15:36,660
<i>Besides, Sayaka is still young.</i>

171
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:44,730
This must be why Sakuraba was so critical.

172
00:15:44,730 --> 00:15:49,600
<i>You're the one who poisoned the bride,
are you not?</i>

173
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:57,440
The adult has to make the first move, right?

174
00:15:59,940 --> 00:16:03,140
Sapphire? Sapphire!

175
00:16:03,140 --> 00:16:05,060
Why are you ignoring my texts?

176
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:08,150
Is this how you show your gratitude?

177
00:16:08,150 --> 00:16:09,010
Answer me!

178
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:10,020
Please, stop that.

179
00:16:10,020 --> 00:16:12,840
What the hell? Who are you? Let me go.

180
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:15,590
I am Sakuraba's friend.

181
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:18,350
You're only bothering him, miss.

182
00:16:18,350 --> 00:16:22,860
This is between me and Sapphire.
Stay out of our business.

183
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:25,630
Open up, Sapphire!

184
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:27,310
You must be a stalker.

185
00:16:27,310 --> 00:16:29,470
What? Stalker?

186
00:16:29,470 --> 00:16:34,850
If you continue to make a ruckus,
I'll be calling the police.

187
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:39,910
F-Fine, I'll leave for now.

188
00:16:39,910 --> 00:16:42,350
The police? Rude.

189
00:16:42,350 --> 00:16:45,460
- If I see you again, I'll be reporting you.
- What the...

190
00:17:12,610 --> 00:17:15,150
[Sapphire Sakuraba]

191
00:17:20,450 --> 00:17:22,080
It's freezing out here.

192
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:34,210
Did you... happen to bump into anyone?

193
00:17:34,210 --> 00:17:36,170
Are you talking about that stalker?

194
00:17:38,550 --> 00:17:41,800
I threatened to report her
the next time I see her.

195
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:47,600
Thank you.

196
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,430
No problem.

197
00:17:51,610 --> 00:17:53,600
Want to come in?

198
00:17:54,260 --> 00:17:56,020
It's cold out there.

199
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:05,310
Thanks.

200
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,450
I'm sorry I doubted you.

201
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,230
For?

202
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:29,160
For spreading rumors about my wedding.

203
00:18:30,980 --> 00:18:33,110
I figured it out.

204
00:18:33,110 --> 00:18:37,090
You had no hand in it, right?

205
00:18:38,180 --> 00:18:41,010
I'm glad that's been cleared up.

206
00:18:42,590 --> 00:18:44,390
And one more thing.

207
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,990
I gave your accusations some thought.

208
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:54,100
I...

209
00:18:56,110 --> 00:18:58,860
I married Sayaka
because I wanted to protect her.

210
00:19:01,020 --> 00:19:04,170
I wasn't the one who poisoned her.

211
00:19:04,170 --> 00:19:06,170
Believe me.

212
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,390
I...

213
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,490
I love Sayaka, with all my heart.

214
00:19:16,710 --> 00:19:19,560
Did you have a talk with her?

215
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:29,400
I've decided to accept Sayaka
for who she is.

216
00:19:32,190 --> 00:19:34,540
Is that so.

217
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:35,970
Sakuraba.

218
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:40,670
I will choose to believe the Sayaka I know.

219
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:42,570
I want to believe in her.

220
00:19:45,650 --> 00:19:52,170
I want to figure out who poisoned Sayaka,
for the sake of our future together.

221
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:56,850
The reason I pushed for another ceremony

222
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:00,800
was because I wanted our wedding
to be a happy memory for her.

223
00:20:02,130 --> 00:20:03,910
I mean it.

224
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:23,220
I should also apologize.

225
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:35,460
I feel silly for doubting a softie like you.

226
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:47,930
I suppose that goes for us both, huh?

227
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,800
I suppose so.

228
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:55,940
I admit, I got heated when you suspected me.

229
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:01,420
But if I never had your help...

230
00:21:03,020 --> 00:21:06,610
I wouldn't have noticed a thing.

231
00:21:07,270 --> 00:21:09,460
Now, I'm more certain than ever.

232
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:14,380
I need your help, Sakuraba.

233
00:21:17,020 --> 00:21:21,040
So please...

234
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:29,850
Join me in searching for the culprit again.

235
00:21:31,220 --> 00:21:38,260
I don't think I'd find anything on my own.

236
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:43,240
I was worried you wouldn't.

237
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:46,320
Well...

238
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:51,550
I've already come this far.

239
00:21:51,550 --> 00:21:57,250
Let me see this case through to its end.

240
00:21:59,450 --> 00:22:06,100
To think I'd get so invested
in someone else's business.

241
00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:13,700
Thank you!

242
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:16,170
I knew you were a good man!

243
00:22:16,170 --> 00:22:17,930
Again?

244
00:22:17,930 --> 00:22:20,360
Sakuraba, thank you!

245
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:22,680
Hayashida.

246
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:24,560
You're choking me.

247
00:22:24,560 --> 00:22:25,540
Could you let me go?

248
00:22:25,540 --> 00:22:26,630
No.

249
00:22:26,630 --> 00:22:27,410
Then leave.

250
00:22:27,410 --> 00:22:28,950
Not happening!

251
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,220
I'm home.

252
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:57,150
Sayaka?

253
00:23:03,670 --> 00:23:06,350
Sayaka? Sayaka!

254
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,540
Sayaka!

255
00:23:09,130 --> 00:23:10,670
Sayaka!

256
00:23:10,670 --> 00:23:12,590
Sayaka!

257
00:23:12,590 --> 00:23:14,780
Sayaka...
